SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 68-1-109, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
(d)
(1) The department of health, in collaboration with the division of
TennCare and the health facilities commission, shall submit an annual report to
the clerk of the senate and the clerk of the house of representatives no later than
August 1, 2025, and by each August 1 thereafter, related to uncompensated care
in this state.
(2) The report required by subdivision (d)(1) must include, but is not
limited to, the following for the most recent calendar year for which complete data
is available:
(A) The amount of public funds distributed by departments or
agencies of this state which were received by facilities that accept
compensation for losses due to providing uncompensated care. This
amount includes funds received by a facility from the virtual
disproportionate share hospital (DSH) fund, uncompensated care
payments for charity patients, and other state funds that distribute
compensation for uncompensated care; and
(B) The total cost of healthcare services classified as
uncompensated care that were provided by each facility that accepts
