public funds for losses due to providing uncompensated care, for which
no payment or partial payment was received from the patient or on behalf
of the patient.
(3) The commissioner of health, in collaboration with the director of
TennCare and the executive director of the health facilities commission, or their
designees, shall present the findings of the report required by this subsection (d)
to the health and welfare committee of the senate and the committee of the
house of representatives having jurisdiction over health-related matters no later
than March 30, 2026, and by March 15 of each subsequent year.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
